<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>

<section xml:id="sec-section-name" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title>Binary and Exploding Dots</title>

  <p>
    Watch the video below before doing <xref ref="activity-1-2-first"/>.
  </p>
  <video youtube="vstIoER3idM"/>
  <activity xml:id="activity-1-2-first">
    <statement>
      <p>
        What is the <m>1 \to 2</m> machine's code for 23?
        <ol marker="A.">
          <li>11101</li>
          <li>10111</li>
          <li>11011</li>
          <li>11111</li>
        </ol>
      </p>
    </statement>
  </activity>
  <activity>
    <statement>
      <p>
        How many is a single dot in the <m>k</m>th box <em>from the right</em> worth?
        <ol marker="A.">
          <li><m>2(k - 1)</m></li>
          <li><m>2k</m></li>
          <li><m>2^{k-1}</m></li>
          <li><m>2^k</m></li>
        </ol>
      </p>
    </statement>
  </activity>
  <activity>
    <statement>
      <p>
        What number does the <m>1 \to 2</m> code <m>1001~0110</m> represent?
        <ol marker="A.">
          <li>142</li>
          <li>144</li>
          <li>150</li>
          <li>158</li>
        </ol>
      </p>
    </statement>
  </activity>
  <activity xml:id="activity-1-2-last">
    <statement>
      <p>
        What is the biggest number a <m>1 \to 2</m> machine with four slots can represent? Eight slots?
      </p>
    </statement>
  </activity>
  <p>
    Watch the video below before doing <xref ref="activity-1-3"/>.
  </p>
  <video youtube="Ok1by1WmmUc"/>
  <activity xml:id="activity-1-3">
    <statement>
      <p>
        Do <xref first="activity-1-2-first" last="activity-1-2-last"/> for the <m>1 \to 3</m> machine
        instead of the <m>1 \to 2</m> machine.
      </p>
    </statement>
  </activity>
  <p>
    Watch the video below before doing <xref ref="activity-1-10"/>.
  </p>
  <video youtube="8t2BDaszWmc"/>
  <activity xml:id="activity-1-10">
    <statement>
      <p>
        Do <xref first="activity-1-2-first" last="activity-1-2-last"/> for the <m>1 \to 10</m> machine
        instead of the <m>1 \to 2</m> machine.
      </p>
    </statement>
  </activity>
  <activity>
    <introduction>
      <p>
        To perform addition using a <m>1 \to 2</m> machine, simply put the codes into a machine
        together, then perform the explosions.
      </p>
    </introduction>
    <task>
      <statement>
        <p>
          Show how you add <m>4 + 6 = 10</m> in a <m>1 \to 2</m> machine.
        </p>
      </statement>
    </task>
    <task>
      <statement>
        <p>
          Show how you add <m>19 + 17 = 36</m> in a <m>1 \to 2</m> machine.
        </p>
      </statement>
    </task>
    <task>
      <statement>
        <p>
          Now let's switch to the <m>1 \to 10</m> machine. Use one to add
          <m>385 + 719 = 1104</m>. Then perform the addition the traditional
          way. What do you notice? Designate a reporter to give your idea to the big group.
        </p>
      </statement>
    </task>
  </activity>
</section>
